{"TopicId":149826,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Landertrons (Automatic Landing Retro-Rockets) v1.3.0 (02021 Sep 06)","CreatedByName":"Kerbas_ad_astra","CreatedById":126593,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T23:11:59Z","PageNum":6,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-31T14:54:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would think it\u0027s something that would have to be baked into the engine, not the controller - and the controller can throttle back down if the engines are throttle-able.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might be something you could add as a part upgrade or as an advanced version of the part for the all-in-one \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003ESRB\u003C/abbr\u003E landing engines however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-01T01:17:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223764008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149826\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585666127\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126593\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbas_ad_astra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Kerbas_ad_astra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...Well, don\u0027t keep me waiting, I wanna see it!\u00A0 I\u0027m not inclined to change the controller, but if it\u0027s technologically straightforward, I might add an \u0027advanced\u0027 controller to take advantage of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll I can tell you is that I\u0027ve come across references to throttleable SRBs that were not baked-in types, that Scott Manley has talked about it in one of his videos (possibly the one where he was invited along with some other youtubers to the progress reveal of KSP2), and that the KSP2 team intend to have them in-game. If I recall correctly, it involves using steerable baffles to redirect the rocket exhaust, similar to the way a jet engine does to produce reverse thrust. More than that, you\u0027d have to research yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-01T01:19:18Z\u0022 title=\u002204/01/2020 01:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 1, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by JAFO\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phoenix-D","CreatedById":9395,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-21T22:23:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmall problem in 1.8.1- the landertrons are arming on stating regardless of what stage they are in. Easy to work around via manually disarming them. Although they were almost a good JATO for that spaceplane launch...hmm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nre throttleable SRBs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1133863879\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/toughsf/status/1130242478085484544\u0022 style=\u0022height:80px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RandomKerbal","CreatedById":206026,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-07-25T18:31:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223789039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149826\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590099782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00229395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phoenix-D\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/22/2020 at 6:23 AM, Phoenix-D said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nre throttleable SRBs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9762741803\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/toughsf/status/1130242478085484544\u0022 style=\u0022height:585px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of the Aluminium Hybrid \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003ESRB\u003C/abbr\u003E from Interstellar Extended.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-07-25T18:33:30Z\u0022 title=\u002207/25/2020 06:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 25, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RandomKerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbas_ad_astra","CreatedById":126593,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-06T19:13:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust as KSP has had its final major release, \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Kerbas-ad-astra/XTLandertron/releases/tag/v1.3.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EXT Landertron 1.3.0 \u0022KISS\u0022\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E is here!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nUpdated part configs to use KSP\u0027s stock EVA construction system. (Also had to recompile the DLL, so this version should only be used with KSP 1.12.x!)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed a few config errors.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"}]}